In article <richardrCqGtzy.J0M@netcom.com> richardr@netcom.com (Richard L. Robertson) writes:

  > You might consider looking at the "subtract-with-borrow" generator
  > developed by George Marsaglia ("A New Class of Randon Number
  > Generator", G.  Marsaglia and Z.Zammar, The Annals of Applied
  > Probability, 1991, Vol 1, Num 1, pp.462-480) as source of of
  > generators of sequences that have lengths >10**200 and which pass
  > all the the standard tests for for randomness.

   These generators have some nice features, but cryptographic
usability is not among them.  There is a neat paper on how to find a
linear congruential generator (with a large modulus) that generates
the same sequence times a constant.


